{"questionId":"9070905","questionHtml":"<p>Which substance is likely to have an ionic lattice structure at 298 K and 100 kPa?</p>\n<table style=\"height:145px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"493\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"4\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:18.4722px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:120.174px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Melting point</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:336.528px;text-align:center;\"><strong>Conducts electricity in a liquid state?</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:18.4722px;\">A.&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:120.174px;\">low</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:336.528px;\">yes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:18.4722px;\">B.</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:120.174px;\">low</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:336.528px;\">no</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:18.4722px;\">C.</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:120.174px;\">high</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:336.528px;\">no</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:18.4722px;\">D.</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:120.174px;\">high</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;width:336.528px;\">yes</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070905","referenceCode":"23M.1.HL.TZ1.9","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Which substance is likely to have an ionic lattice structure at 298 K and 100 kPa? Melting point Conducts electricity in a liquid state? A. low yes B. low no C. high no D. high yes","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"9","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","1.1 Introduction to the particulate nature of matter and chemical change","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}